    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks, that looks solid. i just want to make it feel a little less \"templatey\" though. can you add a sentence or two that acknowledges how much work they put into the technical assessment specifically? they spent like 4 hours on our take-home test so i want them to feel like we actually valued that effort, even if it didn't result in a hire.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That's a smart move; acknowledging the effort on the take-home test shows you actually *saw* their work, not just their resume. You can weave that in right after you praise their technical skills.\n\nHere is the revised version, with a specific nod to their dedication on the assessment. It feels much more tailored now, which is important when rejecting someone who performed well.\n\n***\n\n**Subject: Update on the Senior Developer Role at [Company Name]**\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you so much for taking the time to interview with our team for the Senior Developer position. We truly enjoyed getting to know you, and we were exceptionally impressed with your technical skills throughout the final rounds. We especially want to acknowledge the significant effort you put into the take-home assessment—four hours is a serious commitment, and your dedication to that challenge did not go unnoticed.\n\nThe caliber of candidates this year was exceptionally high, which made our decision incredibly difficult. After careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose specific experience aligned slightly more closely with the immediate needs of this particular role. This was a tough call, as your background is genuinely impressive.\n\nWe sincerely appreciate the time and effort you invested in",
      "source": "target",
